channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: Energy-Guided Diffusion Sampling for Offline-to-Online Reinforcement Learning
item.description: Combining offline and online reinforcement learning (RL) techniques is indeed crucial for achieving efficient and safe learning where data acquisition is expensive.

item.title: Dual-Hybrid Attention Network for Specular Highlight Removal
item.description: Specular highlight removal plays a pivotal role in multimedia applications, as it enhances the quality and interpretability of images and videos, ultimately improving the performance of downstream tasks such as content-based retrieval, object recognition, and scene understanding.

item.title: CerberusDet: Unified Multi-Task Object Detection
item.description: Object detection is a core task in computer vision.

item.title: SG-NeRF: Neural Surface Reconstruction with Scene Graph Optimization
item.description: To tackle this challenge, we present a novel approach that optimizes radiance fields with scene graphs to mitigate the influence of outlier poses.

item.title: Patch-Level Training for Large Language Models
item.description: As Large Language Models (LLMs) achieve remarkable progress in language understanding and generation, their training efficiency has become a critical concern.

item.title: IMAGDressing-v1: Customizable Virtual Dressing
item.description: Latest advances have achieved realistic virtual try-on (VTON) through localized garment inpainting using latent diffusion models, significantly enhancing consumers' online shopping experience.

item.title: Sharif-STR at SemEval-2024 Task 1: Transformer as a Regression Model for Fine-Grained Scoring of Textual Semantic Relations
item.description: Our study focuses on assessing the efficacy of this approach across different languages.

item.title: E5-V: Universal Embeddings with Multimodal Large Language Models
item.description: We propose a single modality training approach for E5-V, where the model is trained exclusively on text pairs.

item.title: Towards Understanding Unsafe Video Generation
item.description: With the labeled information and the corresponding prompts, we created the first dataset of unsafe videos generated by VGMs.

item.title: Fast Context-Based Low-Light Image Enhancement via Neural Implicit Representations
item.description: Current deep learning-based low-light image enhancement methods often struggle with high-resolution images, and fail to meet the practical demands of visual perception across diverse and unseen scenarios.

item.title: HGL: Hierarchical Geometry Learning for Test-time Adaptation in 3D Point Cloud Segmentation
item.description: HGL comprises three complementary modules from local, global to temporal learning in a bottom-up manner. Technically, we first construct a local geometry learning module for pseudo-label generation.

item.title: The Better Angels of Machine Personality: How Personality Relates to LLM Safety
item.description: In this paper, we discover that LLMs' personality traits are closely related to their safety abilities, i. e., toxicity, privacy, and fairness, based on the reliable MBTI-M scale.

item.title: CoSIGN: Few-Step Guidance of ConSIstency Model to Solve General INverse Problems
item.description: Within comparable NFEs, our method achieves new state-of-the-art in diffusion-based inverse problem solving, showcasing the significant potential of employing prior-based inverse problem solvers for real-world applications.

item.title: Leveraging the Mahalanobis Distance to enhance Unsupervised Brain MRI Anomaly Detection
item.description: Unsupervised Anomaly Detection (UAD) methods rely on healthy data distributions to identify anomalies as outliers.

item.title: NavGPT-2: Unleashing Navigational Reasoning Capability for Large Vision-Language Models
item.description: Capitalizing on the remarkable advancements in Large Language Models (LLMs), there is a burgeoning initiative to harness LLMs for instruction following robotic navigation.

item.title: ProcTag: Process Tagging for Assessing the Efficacy of Document Instruction Data
item.description: An effective evaluation method for document instruction data is crucial in constructing instruction data with high efficacy, which, in turn, facilitates the training of LLMs and MLLMs for document VQA.

item.title: High Frequency Matters: Uncertainty Guided Image Compression with Wavelet Diffusion
item.description: We introduce a wavelet conditional diffusion model for high frequency prediction, followed by a residual codec that compresses and transmits prediction residuals to the decoder.

item.title: MoME: Mixture of Multimodal Experts for Generalist Multimodal Large Language Models
item.description: In this paper, we propose a mixture of multimodal experts (MoME) to mitigate task interference and obtain a generalist MLLM.

item.title: Generating 3D House Wireframes with Semantics
item.description: We present a new approach for generating 3D house wireframes with semantic enrichment using an autoregressive model.

item.title: Uncertainty Calibration with Energy Based Instance-wise Scaling in the Wild Dataset
item.description: In this paper, we investigate robust post-hoc uncertainty calibration methods for DNNs within the context of multi-class classification tasks.

item.title: GLARE: Low Light Image Enhancement via Generative Latent Feature based Codebook Retrieval
item.description: Most existing Low-light Image Enhancement (LLIE) methods either directly map Low-Light (LL) to Normal-Light (NL) images or use semantic or illumination maps as guides.

item.title: InfoNorm: Mutual Information Shaping of Normals for Sparse-View Reconstruction
item.description: 3D surface reconstruction from multi-view images is essential for scene understanding and interaction.

item.title: Enhancing Wrist Abnormality Detection with YOLO: Analysis of State-of-the-art Single-stage Detection Models
item.description: Diagnosing and treating abnormalities in the wrist, specifically distal radius, and ulna fractures, is a crucial concern among children, adolescents, and young adults, with a higher incidence rate during puberty.

item.title: PersLLM: A Personified Training Approach for Large Language Models
item.description: Large language models exhibit aspects of human-level intelligence that catalyze their application as human-like agents in domains such as social simulations, human-machine interactions, and collaborative multi-agent systems.

item.title: Benchmarking Robust Self-Supervised Learning Across Diverse Downstream Tasks
item.description: Since the purpose of a foundation model is to cater to multiple applications at once, our findings reveal the need to enhance encoder robustness more broadly.

item.title: EmoFace: Audio-driven Emotional 3D Face Animation
item.description: Our approach can generate facial expressions with multiple emotions, and has the ability to generate random yet natural blinks and eye movements, while maintaining accurate lip synchronization.

item.title: Abstraction Alignment: Comparing Model and Human Conceptual Relationships
item.description: Abstraction -- the process of generalizing specific examples into broad reusable patterns -- is central to how people efficiently process and store information and apply their knowledge to new data.

item.title: LMMs-Eval: Reality Check on the Evaluation of Large Multimodal Models
item.description: To approach this evaluation trilemma, we further introduce LMMS-EVAL LITE, a pruned evaluation toolkit that emphasizes both coverage and efficiency.

item.title: GraphMuse: A Library for Symbolic Music Graph Processing
item.description: Addressing this gap, we present GraphMuse, a graph processing framework and library that facilitates efficient music graph processing and GNN training for symbolic music tasks.

item.title: A Unifying Post-Processing Framework for Multi-Objective Learn-to-Defer Problems
item.description: Although there are currently systems that follow this paradigm and are designed to optimize the accuracy of the final human-AI team, the general methodology for developing such systems under a set of constraints (e. g., algorithmic fairness, expert intervention budget, defer of anomaly, etc.)

item.title: Reliable and Efficient Concept Erasure of Text-to-Image Diffusion Models
item.description: In this work, we introduce Reliable and Efficient Concept Erasure (RECE), a novel approach that modifies the model in 3 seconds without necessitating additional fine-tuning.

item.title: Any Target Can be Offense: Adversarial Example Generation via Generalized Latent Infection
item.description: Notably, compared with other generative methods, our method achieves an approximately $14. 13\%$ higher attack success rate for unknown classes and an approximately $4. 23\%$ higher success rate for known classes.

item.title: Out of Length Text Recognition with Sub-String Matching
item.description: In this paper, we term this the Out of Length (OOL) text recognition.

item.title: COHO: Context-Sensitive City-Scale Hierarchical Urban Layout Generation
item.description: The method encodes attributed buildings, city blocks, communities and cities into a unified graph structure, enabling self-supervised masked training for graph autoencoder.

item.title: Global Optimisation of Black-Box Functions with Generative Models in the Wasserstein Space
item.description: To address these issues, we utilise a deep generative surrogate approach to model the black box response for the entire parameter space.

item.title: PRET: Planning with Directed Fidelity Trajectory for Vision and Language Navigation
item.description: In this work, we propose an alternative method that facilitates navigation planning by considering the alignment between instructions and directed fidelity trajectories, which refers to a path from the initial node to the candidate locations on a directed graph without detours.

item.title: Learning to Make Keypoints Sub-Pixel Accurate
item.description: This work addresses the challenge of sub-pixel accuracy in detecting 2D local features, a cornerstone problem in computer vision.

item.title: Data-Juicer Sandbox: A Comprehensive Suite for Multimodal Data-Model Co-development
item.description: The emergence of large-scale multi-modal generative models has drastically advanced artificial intelligence, introducing unprecedented levels of performance and functionality.

item.title: DreamCatalyst: Fast and High-Quality 3D Editing via Controlling Editability and Identity Preservation
item.description: However, existing SDS-based 3D editing methods suffer from extensive training time and lead to low-quality results, primarily because these methods deviate from the sampling dynamics of diffusion models.

item.title: GV-Bench: Benchmarking Local Feature Matching for Geometric Verification of Long-term Loop Closure Detection
item.description: Existing feature matching methods focus on homography and pose estimation in long-term visual localization, lacking references for geometric verification.

item.title: Enhancing Split Computing and Early Exit Applications through Predefined Sparsity
item.description: This paper introduces a novel approach to address this challenge by combining the concept of predefined sparsity with Split Computing (SC) and Early Exit (EE).

item.title: Not Another Imputation Method: A Transformer-based Model for Missing Values in Tabular Datasets
item.description: Handling missing values in tabular datasets presents a significant challenge in training and testing artificial intelligence models, an issue usually addressed using imputation techniques.

item.title: Learning Confidence Bounds for Classification with Imbalanced Data
item.description: Class imbalance poses a significant challenge in classification tasks, where traditional approaches often lead to biased models and unreliable predictions.

item.title: SDPT: Synchronous Dual Prompt Tuning for Fusion-based Visual-Language Pre-trained Models
item.description: Existing prompt tuning methods have not effectively addressed the modal mapping and aligning problem for tokens in different modalities, leading to poor transfer generalization.

item.title: Relation DETR: Exploring Explicit Position Relation Prior for Object Detection
item.description: The experimental results on the dataset illustrate that the proposed explicit position relation achieves a clear improvement of 1. 3% AP, highlighting its potential towards universal object detection.

item.title: Simplifying the Theory on Over-Smoothing
item.description: Graph convolutions have gained popularity due to their ability to efficiently operate on data with an irregular geometric structure.

item.title: cDP-MIL: Robust Multiple Instance Learning via Cascaded Dirichlet Process
item.description: We then perform bag-level prediction with another Dirichlet process model on the bags, which imposes a natural regularization on learning to prevent overfitting and enhance generalizability.

item.title: HyperAggregation: Aggregating over Graph Edges with Hypernetworks
item.description: We demonstrate HyperAggregation in two models, GraphHyperMixer is a model based on MLP-Mixer while GraphHyperConv is derived from a GCN but with a hypernetwork-based aggregation function.

item.title: Improving Unsupervised Video Object Segmentation via Fake Flow Generation
item.description: Unsupervised video object segmentation (VOS), also known as video salient object detection, aims to detect the most prominent object in a video at the pixel level.

item.title: Exploring Quantization for Efficient Pre-Training of Transformer Language Models
item.description: While quantization has proven to be effective after pre-training and during fine-tuning, applying quantization in Transformers during pre-training has remained largely unexplored at scale for language modeling.
